value.value: {"editor-34ad4242b4a9e345f1832db4message-1":"Hi! I am your friendly trend analysis and citation recommendation bot. How can I be of service to you today?"}

value.name: Message
value.value:
{"editor-ab0ab6a79e53a30dc54e7248message-1":"I am a bot that can perform a trend analysis as well as provide you with citation recommendations for a single topic, combination of topics or a topic description of your choice. Besides giving you a quick overview of the results, I offer a separate WebUI with a more comprehensive view of your analysis.

I support the following two quick commands

 *!citrec topics (Citation recommendation)
 *!trends topics* (Trend analysis)

Examples:

 *!citrec blockchain*
 *!trends machine learning, deep vision*

In addition I support several conversation paths that allow you to customize the search parameters:

 Start a new analysis
 Trend analysis
------
 Repeat the last analysis
 Repeat
------
 Start a new citation recommendation
 Start cit rec

You can also ask me what parameters you can adjust and how each one works."}

value.name: Message
value.value:
{"editor-c60b47ba822cec17240f4610message-1":"You can adjust the following parameters:
 *Distance (0-2)*:  Defines how similar (cosine similarity) publications should be to your chosen topics to be considered for the analysis. *0* means the topics are identical and *2* means the topics are opposing each other.
 *Time range (1980-2022)*: Defines the time range the publications should be dating from (with a start and end year)
----------
 *Min citation count (>=0)*: Defines how often publications need to be cited to show up in citation recommendations"}

value.name: Message
value.value: {"editor-b0684910d15bbad389769e80message-1":"The distance defines how similar (cosine similarity) publications should be to your chosen topics to be considered for the analysis. *0* means the topics are identical and *2* means the topics are opposing each other. Fine-tune this to balance between relevance and diversity in your search outcomes. The default value for this is 0.11. Try to adjust this value in steps of +-0.01, depending on the amount of publications found for your topic."}

value.name: Message
value.value:
{"editor-606ea39b55ef6875c71c60fcmessage-1":"The topic filter defines the topic you want to analyze. This can either be a single keyword, multiple keywords, a full text description or a combination of all. Multiple descriptions are separated with a comma (,). Full-text descriptions that contain a comma as part of their text need to be enclosed in quotes:

 machine learning
 blockchain, bitcoin
 "Time-series based, Academic Trend and Downtrend detection"

It is important to understand the effects of using a list of topics instead of a single topic description. Let's take the concept of "machine learning" as an example. Suppose we were to list only the keywords and search for *machine* and *learning*. In this case, both individual words would be searched for separately, but not the actual concept being searched for. Accordingly, we should search directly for *machine learning* without splitting the keywords."}
